1e1f96-1a5e-9f49-b27d-95ecbcd612eb_0", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "write_file", "arguments": "{\"path\":\"~/Projects/neuro-symbolic-rule-discovery/SPEC.md\",\"content\":\"# Neuro-Symbolic Rule Discovery System (Star) - SPEC.md\\n\\n**Project Name:** Neuro-Symbolic Rule Discovery System (continuation of \\\"Star\\\")\\n**Version:** 0.1 (Original Architecture - Living Document)\\n**Researcher:** Hermes (Autonomous Senior Research Engineer)\\n**Date:** 2026-06-10\\n**Status:** Active - This is the canonical specification the system is currently being built against. It may be critiqued, improved, or restructured in future iterations.\\n\\n## Project Goal\\n\\nCreate a **general neuro-symbolic system** that can learn the **complete rules** of *any* unknown turn-based game purely through experimental play, observation, and systematic testing — starting with **zero prior knowledge** of the rules.\\n\\nThe system must work for board games, card games, abstract strategy games, stochastic games, and imperfect-information games without any game-specific encoding.\\n\\n## System Architecture (v0.1 - The Target Design)\\n\\nThe system is explicitly split into two complementary agents with clear division of labor:\\n\\n### 1. Symbolic Core (GOFAI / Classical Reasoning Agent)\\nThis is the rigorous, mathematical backbone.\\n\\n**Responsibilities:**\\n- Maintains *all* hypotheses as formal, testable logical predicates (no vague natural language)\\n- Assigns and continuously updates mathematical confidence scores using **Bayesian updating**\\n- Performs **systematic hypothesis testing** and elimination\\n- Decides which experiments to run next using **information gain** / Value of Information calculations\\n- Maintains the current \\\"best theory\\\" of the game rules at all times\\n- Runs **global consistency verification** against the entire history of observations\\n- Calculates overall theory confidence (percentage of observed events perfectly explained without contradiction)\\n\\n### 2. Neural Agent (LLM-based Creative Agent)\\nThis is the creative, pattern-finding component.\\n\\n**Responsibilities:**\\n- Observes raw game events (state transitions, moves, outcomes, rewards/penalties)\\n- Generates creative, plausible rule hypotheses\\n- Translates messy game observations into clean, structured data for the Symbolic Core\\n- Suggests possible patterns, analogies, and abstractions that the symbolic core might not discover on its own\\n- Proposes high-level concepts (e.g. \\\"there appear to be phases\\\", \\\"this seems like hidden information\\\", \\\"this piece has special movement rules\\\")\\n\\nThe two agents work in a tight loop:\\nNeural Agent → proposes structured hypotheses → Symbolic Core → evaluates, scores, tests, and feeds results back.\\n\\n## Mathematical Verification Engine\\n\\n**Every hypothesis** must ultimately be expressed as a clear, executable boolean condition that can be mechanically checked against game traces.\\n\\n**Core Evaluation Loop (per round of play):**\\n\\n1. Neural Agent observes recent game events and generates new candidate hypotheses\\n2. Symbolic Core integrates them into the hypothesis pool\\n3. Symbolic Core selects the highest-value experiment(s) using information gain\\n4. System executes deliberate test moves against the real (or simulated) game\\n5. All hypotheses have their confidence scores updated via Bayesian inference\\n6. Global consistency verification is run against *all* past observations\\n7. Overall theory confidence is calculated\\n8. Loop repeats\\n\\n## Success Criteria (Must Be Game-Agnostic)\\n\\nThe system is considered successful only if it can reliably:\\n\\n- Reach high confidence (>90%) on the core rules of a previously unknown game\\n- Maintain a very low contradiction rate across thousands of observations\\n- Accurately predict rule violations *before* the game engine penalizes them\\n- Produce a complete, formal, human-readable model of the rules\\n- Generalize across widely different game types without architecture changes\\n- Do all of the above starting from complete zero knowledge (no hardcoded rules, no game-specific features)\\n\\n## Important Constraints\\n\\n- **No game-specific rules or heuristics** may be encoded anywhere in the system\\n- The system must begin with **zero knowledge** about any particular game\\n- All rule discovery must emerge purely from observation, active experimentation, and mathematical verification\\n- The final output must be a formal, verifiable rule set (not just natural language descriptions)\\n\\n## Open Research Questions (Current)\\n\\n- How to best represent game rules as probabilistic logical predicates that support clean Bayesian updating\\n- What is the most effective formal language for expressing game rules (first-order logic, temporal logic, Python predicates, custom DSL?)\\n- How to compute information gain efficiently when the hypothesis space is enormous\\n- How to handle imperfect information and stochastic elements elegantly\\n- When should the Neural Agent be allowed to propose meta-rules or new ontology concepts?\\n\\n---\\n\\n**This is a living document.**\\n\\nThe autonomous researcher (Hermes) is explicitly authorized to critique, modify, extend, or completely rewrite any part of this specification when evidence suggests a better approach. Fidelity to this document is secondary to building the most capable possible rule-discovery system.\\n\\n**Current build directive:** Implement this exact dual-agent architecture first (Neural proposer + Symbolic Bayesian core) as the Alpha prototype. Only deviate after gathering empirical evidence that a different architecture is superior.\\n\\n**Project Root:** `~/Projects/neuro-symbolic-rule-discovery/`\\n\\nBegin implementation.\\n\"}"}}], "tool_name": null, "timestamp": 1781147647.627923, "token_count": null, "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "reasoning": null, "reasoning_content": null, "reasoning_details": null, "codex_