ortant.\n\nSo the system must be able to:\n1. Generate plausible hypotheses about what might matter.\n2. Test or gather evidence for those hypotheses.\n3. Update its understanding of the task boundary itself.\n4. Do this without exploding in cost or time.\n5. Avoid hallucinating fake constraints.\n\nThis is adjacent to concepts like:\n- Active Inference / Bayesian Experimental Design\n- Reflective / Self-Improving Agents\n- Meta-Learning of User Intent\n- \"Research Agent\" or \"Investigative Agent\" patterns\n\n---\n\n**Question for you:**\n\nBefore I propose any specific architecture or mechanism, I want to understand your desired outcome more clearly.\n\nWhat would \"success\" look like for this system?\n\nFor example:\n- When you give it a vague task like \"make an n8n workflow that advertises on reddit\", what level of implicit context discovery would feel like a breakthrough to you?\n- How much of this discovery should be autonomous vs collaborative with you?\n- Should it produce a \"context map\" before starting the actual work?\n- Or should it silently absorb the context and just produce much better outputs?\n\nTell me what your ideal version of this would feel like in practice. The more precise you can be about the desired behavior, the better I can help design it.", "tool_call_id": null, "tool_calls": null, "tool_name": null, "timestamp": 1780879964.739715, "token_count": null, "finish_reason": "stop", "reasoning": null, "reasoning_content": null, "reasoning_details": null, "codex_reasoning_items": null, "codex_message_items": "[{\"type\": \"message\", \"role\": \"assistant\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"output_text\", \"text\": \"**Yes.**\\n\\nYou just named the real thing you're trying to build.\\n\\n### The Actual Goal\\n\\nYou are trying to create **an agentic system that can systematically discover and incorporate the \\\"unknown unknowns\\\" surrounding any task** \\u2014 especially the implicit, personal, stylistic, histori